CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778051113
OL,3,CKeir Starmer vows to round off local
OL,4,Celection campaign 'fighting for every
OL,5,Cvote'
OL,7,FSpeaking to the Press Association,
OL,8,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,9,Falso listed areas he expected his
OL,10,Fparty to take seats.
OL,12,F"I'm looking forward to next
OL,13,FThursday," he told PA.
OL,15,F"I think we're going to make some
OL,16,Freally big gains in London where I
OL,17,Fthink we'll take seats off the Labour
OL,18,FParty and indeed off Labour in places
OL,19,Flike Birmingham and Scotland.
OL,26,@tD@AOUuD@JO]wD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778051113
OL,3,CKeir Starmer vows to round off local
OL,4,Celection campaign 'fighting for every
OL,5,Cvote'
OL,7,F"But I do think across the south of
OL,8,FEngland ` Surrey and Sussex,
OL,9,FHampshire, Hertfordshire,
OL,10,FHuntingdonshire, we're going to make
OL,11,Fbig gains from the Conservatives.
OL,13,F"So, we're looking forward to a good
OL,14,Fnight on Thursday."
OL,16,FReform UK leader Nigel Farage spent
OL,17,FTuesday evening in Merthyr Tydfil,
OL,18,Fwhere he said Wales had become a
OL,19,F"basket case" after being led by
OL,20,FLabour for more than two decades.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUvD@SO]{D@AOU{D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778051113
OL,3,CKeir Starmer vows to round off local
OL,4,Celection campaign 'fighting for every
OL,5,Cvote'
OL,7,F"The party that has been able,
OL,8,Ffrankly, to take Wales for granted for
OL,9,Fover 100 years on Thursday will
OL,10,Fdeservedly get smashed to smithereens
OL,11,Fby the electorate," he said.
OL,13,FMr Farage, whose party's election
OL,14,Fcampaign slogan is "Vote Reform, get
OL,15,FStarmer out", added: "Getting rid of
OL,16,FStarmer will begin the descending
OL,17,Fspiral of this Government.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@SO]vD@TOUwD@LO]wD@VOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778051113
OL,3,CKeir Starmer vows to round off local
OL,4,Celection campaign 'fighting for every
OL,5,Cvote'
OL,7,F"The realisation that our economy is
OL,8,Fbroken, that the country is, frankly,
OL,9,Fbankrupt, and will precipitate an
OL,10,Fearlier general election.
OL,12,F"And I still believe that a general
OL,13,Felection next year is likely."
OL,15,FGreen Party leader Zack Polanski
OL,16,Fdescribed Thursday's votes as "a vital
OL,17,Fset of elections".
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUuD@^O]xD@_OUyD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
